<br>
&quot;For YOU, Mr. Blademaster, the game takes an average of Celtic Dual and your weapon spec. And since you are 40th, and your average spec in the two areas is 30, you are currently running better than optimal. &quot;<br>
<br>
If you read the whole question, it concerns the damage that a blademaster does.  In that grab bag, we are told that the damage a blademaster does is determined by the average of his weapon skill and his celtic dual skill.  So I respecced accordingly.<br>
<br>
NOW.....  In the latest grab bag of 2003-01-10, we are told, among other things:<br>
<br>
&quot;Your spec in Celtic Duel determines only the percentage chance of you getting a second swing during that round of combat. Celtic Duel has nothing to do with the damage either swing can do.&quot;<br>
<br>
So, pardon my French, but wtf?  I respecced because I was told one thing last August.  Now, Mythic has forgotten all about what they said in August, and have just said something totally completely and different in January.  Of course, my questions to Mythic have remained unanswered and unacknowledged.<br>
<br>
So... I am posting this glaring discrepancy here in the hopes that SOMEONE from Mythic who knows anything might be perusing this board and might be kind enough to grace me with some sort of explanation.  Because I would really like one.  If I buggered up my blademaster because of erroneous information given to us last August, I would sort of like a respec so I can fix it.  I don't think that that request is too unreasonable at all.<br>
<br>
Thank you for your support.<br>
